{"Body":"<p>I read that PIE, Latin, old English, and even old German did not use articles, yet current English, German and Romance languages all use articles.</p>\n\n<p>Is it true that articles developed in all these languages independently from the word for \"one\"? What is the reason for their development? Were they useful in any way, such as helping pronunciation?</p>\n", "Id":"3596", "LastEditorUserId":"1983", "AcceptedAnswerId":"3620", "Title":"Origin of articles in European languages", "CreationDate":"2013-04-21T21:19:51.427", "OwnerUserId":"1983", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<historical-linguistics><indo-european><articles>", "AnswerCount":"3", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-04-22T12:52:17.140", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"6", "WebsiteUrl":"http://coding-time.blogspot.com", "Id":"1983", "AccountId":"32719", "CreationDate":"2013-04-21T21:11:56.820", "AboutMe":"<p><a href=\"http://martinkonicek.net\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://martinkonicek.net</a></p>\n", "Age":"28", "Location":"Berlin, Germany", "DownVotes":"0", "Views":"1", "Reputation":"123", "DisplayName":"Martin Konicek", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-04T15:52:10.583"}, "ViewCount":"342", "LastActivityDate":"2013-05-05T20:18:22.467", "Score":"4", "CommentCount":"6", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"6", "WebsiteUrl":"http://coding-time.blogspot.com", "Id":"1983", "AccountId":"32719", "CreationDate":"2013-04-21T21:11:56.820", "AboutMe":"<p><a href=\"http://martinkonicek.net\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://martinkonicek.net</a></p>\n", "Age":"28", "Location":"Berlin, Germany", "DownVotes":"0", "Views":"1", "Reputation":"123", "DisplayName":"Martin Konicek", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-04T15:52:10.583"}}